<item>
            <title>[HBASE-1108] Redundant meta tables</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1108</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the data file for &lt;del&gt;ROOT&lt;/del&gt; or .META. is damaged, a HBase installation is rendered inoperative. Manual recovery through writing a new &lt;del&gt;ROOT&lt;/del&gt; by hand is relatively simple (I think) but it&apos;s not simple and maybe not even possible to recreate a .META. containing thousands of regions. During one experiment I lost the entire .META. data file due to DFS errors during compaction. This can be avoided by utilizing multiple backing data files for &lt;del&gt;ROOT&lt;/del&gt; and .META. synchronized in a manner that avoids total data loss should the filesystem become degraded. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
